When your user logging in, if the user logged in successfully before you redirect user just save his user somewhere, one of your options is saving users data in local storage like this

    localStorage.setItem(&quot;user&quot;, user);

The first &quot;user&quot; is a name that you define, the second user is your argument that you get users info, so it creates a data in your browser storage and you can use it in other pages.
So in your welcome page, just use this  :

    Const user=localStorage.getItem(&quot;user&quot;);

And in your render just make a div and write 

&gt; welcome {user}

I hope you get the idea and it works well for you.
Ps. If you use chrome you can inspect your page and go to the application tab and see your saved data in local storage.

